This paper is primarily focused on exploring the efficiency of convolutional polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of these codes in communication systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves numerical simulations and explores the efficiency of different coding schemes, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of convolutional polar codes in wireless communication systems, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
